<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORCYCLE COMMUTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Why does this debate about a mandatory helmet law exist? Answer: the insurance 
industry (who else?). If the insurance people would get their act together and 
triple the medical premiums for those motorcyclists who choose not to wear a 
helmet (to reflect the much higher costs of an accident), I'm sure the cyclists 
would decide having the wind in your hair isn't that important after all. 
</P>
<P>
DAVE DeHERAS 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
