<HEADLINE>
<P>
ETHNIC CONFLICT IN EAST BLOC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I disagree with the observation by McManus. McManus states that nationalism is 
dangerous. On the contrary, I feel it is the healthiest omen experienced by not 
only the East Bloc countries but specifically the Soviet Republic. 
</P>
<P>
Nationalism has always existed there in spite of the Russians' insistence on 
developing the robotic "Soviet Man" -- devoid of a heritage, history, culture, 
etc. This plot did not work as we can see. The underlying nationalism is being 
recognized. 
</P>
<P>
I spent the last 1 1/2 years in the Soviet Union's non-Russian republics and 
what I saw and heard was truly positive. The people are full of hope -- maybe 
for the first time in 70 years. All their energies are being applied to 
throwing off the Russians once and for all -- and these were not the Baltic 
republics either. 
</P>
<P>
ERIC McHUGH 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
