<HEADLINE>
<P>
ETHNIC CONFLICT IN EAST BLOC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zbigniew Brzezinski may be perilously correct in declaring that ". . . the 
national and ethnic animosities in Eastern Europe and the Soviet Union . . . 
could result in . . . geopolitical anarchy." Which is why we should be wary of 
naming Mikhail Gorbachev savior before the facts are all in. 
</P>
<P>
It could be that the turmoil his reforms are causing within the Communist world 
will result in civil war within the Soviet Union and -- who knows? -- nuclear 
war with others. When there are too many fingers on too many buttons . . . 
</P>
<P>
JIM REAGAN 
</P>
<P>
Norwalk 
</P>
</TEXT>
