<P>
PEOPLE: TIMES PROMOTES 2 TO VICE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times has promoted Paul Gledhill, director of production, to 
the new position of vice president-production, and Mike Williams, director of 
information systems, to the new position of vice president-systems and 
administration. 
</P>
<P>
Gledhill, 48, continues to be responsible for The Times' 3,000-member 
production department, including operations at the newspaper's San Fernando 
Valley, Orange County and downtown Los Angeles plants. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to information systems, which includes virtually all of The Times' 
computer and telecommunications operations, Williams, 46, now oversees the 
newspaper's administrative services and technical services departments. 
</P>
