<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KENNEDY MEETS THE CHALLENGE WITH VICTORY OVER PACIFICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA PALMA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After losing its first Garden Grove League game of the season, Kennedy High 
School Coach John Mayberry issued a challenge to his players, telling them 
their "magic number was 13." 
</P>
<P>
And despite a slow start and making only 33% of their shots from the field 
Friday night at Kennedy, the Fighting Irish met Mayberry's challenge. They 
completed league play with their 13th victory, a 55-48 triumph over Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy's victory, coupled with Rancho Alamitos' 78-64 victory over Bolsa 
Grande Friday, placed the teams in a tie for the Garden Grove League 
championship. Both teams finished with 13-1 records in league play, splitting 
their two games against each other. 
</P>
<P>
"Before the game tonight, I told the kids that if they don't win this one, the 
other 12 don't mean anything," Mayberry said. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy came out tight, making only four of 15 shots in the first quarter, and 
fell behind Pacifica 15-10 after one quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Forward Jim Barker's game-high 25 points, 13 in the first half, kept Kennedy 
close early. The Mariners built a 26-23 halftime lead, and Mayberry gave his 
team another challenge. 
</P>
<P>
"I told them at halftime, 'It is your championship to win, "' Mayberry said, 
"'If you want it, go and get it. I have over 200 wins and six championships 
already.' But another one is always nice." 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy responded by scoring 11 points in the first two minutes of the third 
quarter, and Pacifica never threatened again. 
</P>
<P>
Center Jermaine Galloway defended the inside with eight blocks, and Barker made 
six free throws in the final two minutes to seal the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 84, La Quinta 64 -- Forward Mark Perry scored 22 points to pace 
host Garden Grove (10-13, 8-6). Forward Joe Squires added 21 points and center 
Bob Ioja had 19 for Garden Grove. Center Justin Sogoian led La Quinta (2-20, 
2-12) with 15 points. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 78, Bolsa Grande 64 -- Paul Preuss scored 21 points to lead 
Rancho Alamitos, which rallied in the second half. Bolsa Grande led at the 
half, 34-33, but Rancho Alamitos outscored Bolsa Grande, 26-20, in the third 
quarter to take the lead. Rancho Alamitos ends the regular season 20-3, 13-1. 
Hinh Bui scored 25 points for Bolsa Grande (8-13, 6-8). 
</P>
</TEXT>
