<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: APPLE PICKS OLSSON TO HEAD FOREIGN UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apple Computer Inc. has promoted a regional manager to head its European, 
African and Middle Eastern operations. 
</P>
<P>
Soren Olsson, 44, was named president of Apple Computer Europe, replacing 
Michael H. Spindler, who last week was named chief operating officer and 
executive vice president of Apple, which has headquarters in Cupertino, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Olsson had directed Apple's Scandinavian operation since 1984. He assumed the 
position of managing director of Sweden and Northern Europe in 1988, overseeing 
operations in Norway, Denmark, Finland, Iceland, West Germany, Austria and 
several Eastern European countries. 
</P>
<P>
"Soren has the vision and the drive needed to ensure Apple Europe's success in 
a global marketplace," Spindler said in announcing the promotion. 
</P>
