</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The films "Gorillas in the Mist" and "The Bear" will be honored at the fourth 
annual Genesis Awards presented at a luncheon Sunday at the Beverly Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
Other Genesis Awards, given by the Fund for Animals (FFA), will also recognize 
entertainment productions and media people who have contributed to the 
understanding of animal issues. Television shows "L.A. Law" and "Roseanne," 
news commentator Charles Kurault and cartoonist Berke Breathed will also be 
honored. Information: (818) 905-1050. 
</P>
