<P>
SCOUTS WILL COLLECT CANNED FOOD TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thousands of Boy Scouts will go door-to-door today, hoping to find the 
orange-and-white bags that they dropped off last weekend filled with canned 
goods. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Scouts collected more than 810,000 cans of food. This year, the 
goal is a million cans. 
</P>
<P>
Scouting officials believe their food drive is the largest ever held in Orange 
County. 
