<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITAN BASKETBALL ASSISTANT STARR RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Starr, a Cal State Fullerton assistant basketball coach, has resigned 
effective immediately, the school announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Starr, 35, had been a part-time assistant at Nevada Las Vegas for four years 
and had lived in Las Vegas for 12 years before being named at Fullerton in 
July. 
</P>
<P>
Sources at Fullerton said Starr missed Las Vegas and has returned there to look 
for a job, possibly outside of coaching. 
</P>
<P>
Starr could not be reached for comment Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton will make changes in its starting lineup against Pacific tonight in 
an attempt to inject more offense, Coach John Sneed said. 
</P>
<P>
Agee Ward, who started at forward early in the season, will replace Van 
Anderson, Sneed said. Anderson will back up Cedric Ceballos, Sneed said, in a 
move designed to provide Ceballos with some rest during games. Ceballos played 
every minute of two overtime games last week. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BASKETBALL; COACHES; RESIGNATIONS; CALIFORNIA STATE UNIVERSITY AT FULLERTON; 
STARR, KEITH 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
